<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 11:53AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern
Pushmataha and Choctaw Counties through 1230 PM CDT...
At 1153 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 7 miles southeast of Nashoba to 3 miles south of
Oleta to near Soper. Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Hugo...                           Fort Towson...
Sawyer...                         Rattan...
Soper...                          Snow...
Hugo Lake State Park...           Clayton Lake State Park...
Kent...                           Goodland...
Messer...                         Raymond Gary State Park...
Nashoba...                        Oleta...
Cloudy...                         Grant...
Ord...                            Fallon...
Sobol...                          Frogville...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
